projects.title: TrackTrends
projects.summary: Personal Spotify stats, discover tracks, play previews & create playlists. Designed for desktop & mobile. Next.js features such as dynamic routing, middleware & auth utilised. Redux used for state managment. Login with Spotify.

projects.title: Social media site
projects.summary: A full-stack hobby project built for Call of Duty gamers. Login, share & like posts, rank your friends, view statistics & personal notifications with the help of cloud functions. Context api used for state management. Firebase backend. Statistics fetched from rapidapi. Fully responsive. 4 stars on Github.

projects.title: Simple retail site
projects.summary: Retail site with checkout. Last challenge of the Scrimba react boot camp by Bob Ziroll. Rebuilt with Next.js and TailwindCss. Using Redux for state management. Masonry layout.

contact.contactText: If you have an opening or any project that I can contribute to, be sure to reach out.

skillDescription: Solid understanding of HTML, CSS & Javascript. In to React after completing the Scrimba react bootcamp. Big fan of TailwindCss for styling. Often use Firebase for serverless backend, can also use Sanity which this site is powered by. For state management I can use Redux, Context or Recoil. Currently learning Typescript, Framer-Motion and some basics of React Native. Write in VS code.
backgroundInformation: I'm Peter Eriksson, a self-taught front end-developer. Always eager to learn new stuff. I like to play around with new tech and build things that excite me. Fluent in Swedish and English, basic understanding of German. Looking for a role as a React developer.
